defaultTwo physicians invented the term “scepticaemia” They defined it as “an uncommon generalised disorder of low infectivity. Medical school education is likely to confer 
defaultlifelong
default immunity”
default 
defaultP.Skrabanek
default and 
defaultJ.
defaultMcCormick
default, Follies and Fallacies in Medicine, 1989).
default&#xa0;
defaultIn analysing the subject of long term conditions scepticaemia is essential. We must ask always where is the evidence, and where it is offered is it robust or optimistic advocacy?
